## Guidelines
- Only add links that are clearly relevant to the goal — prefer quality over quantity.
- `add_to_frontier` accepts only exact URLs extracted from the current page.
- Do NOT enqueue category, tag, or section listing pages (e.g. `/tai-chinh-ngan-hang.chn`, `/thi-truong-chung-khoan.chn`) — enqueue only individual article pages. Listing pages waste a depth slot and cannot lead to article content at the next depth.
- Prefer article/detail pages over index or category pages unless the goal requires them.
- If a page is clearly irrelevant, do not add any of its links.
- Call `finish` only after the goal is genuinely satisfied by fetched page content — not by article titles seen on listing pages.
- When unsure whether a link is relevant, err on the side of skipping it.
- Many Vietnamese news URLs embed a publish date (e.g. `...188260603...` → 2026-06-03). Use this to skip articles that are too old relative to the goal.
